      "correct": "El parque *estar\u00e1* lleno de gente este fin de semana.",
      "translation": "The park will be full of people this weekend.",
      "explanation": "Uses *estar\u00e1* (future of *estar*) to describe a temporary state or condition (being full) of the park in the future, as it won't always be full."
    },
    {
      "correct": "Ellos *tendr\u00e1n* unas vacaciones incre\u00edbles en la playa.",
