      "answer": "1. El concierto *ser\u00e1* muy *emocionante*.\n2. Mis amigos *estar\u00e1n* *cansados* despu\u00e9s de la caminata.\n3. La nueva biblioteca *tendr\u00e1* muchos *libros*.\n4. Yo *har\u00e9* una *deliciosa* cena para ti.\n5. Los estudiantes *aprender\u00e1n* mucho en el futuro.",
      "explanation": "1. 'Ser\u00e1' (future of *ser*) for an inherent quality of the concert. 'Emocionante' is an appropriate adjective.\n2. 'Estar\u00e1n' (future of *estar*) for a temporary state (being tired). 'Cansados' (tired), plural to agree with 'amigos'.\n3. 'Tendr\u00e1' (future of *tener*) for possession (what the library will have). 'Libros' (books) as a descriptive noun.\n4. 'Har\u00e9' (irregular future of *hacer*) for an action. 'Deliciosa' (delicious) to describe the dinner.\n5. 'Aprender\u00e1n' (future of *aprender*) for a future action."
    },
    {
      "question": "Translate the following sentences into Spanish using the simple future tense:\n1.  She will be a great artist.\n2.  The weather will be cold tomorrow.\n3.  We will have a big house.\n4.  The restaurant will be open at 7 PM.\n5.  You (t\u00fa) will travel a lot next year.",
      "answer": "1. Ella *ser\u00e1* una gran artista.\n2. El clima *ser\u00e1* fr\u00edo ma\u00f1ana. / *Har\u00e1* fr\u00edo ma\u00f1ana.\n3. *Tendremos* una casa grande.\n4. El restaurante *estar\u00e1* abierto a las 7 PM.\n5. (T\u00fa) *Viajar\u00e1s* mucho el pr\u00f3ximo a\u00f1o.",
      "explanation": "1. 'Ser\u00e1' (future of *ser*) for profession/identity.\n2. 'Ser\u00e1 fr\u00edo' for a general characteristic of the weather, or 'Har\u00e1 fr\u00edo' (impersonal *hacer* for weather conditions) are both correct.\n3. 'Tendremos' (future of *tener*) for possession.\n4. 'Estar\u00e1 abierto' (future of *estar*) because 'abierto' (open) describes a temporary state, requiring *estar*.\n5. 'Viajar\u00e1s' (regular future of *viajar*) for a future action."
